OpenLapse Licensing
====================

This repository contains both hardware design files and software. Different licenses apply to each category:

- Hardware (PCB design files, 3D models/STL): CERN Open Hardware License Version 2 – Strongly Reciprocal (CERN-OHL-S-2.0).
- Software (OpenLapse-Controller desktop GUI and OpenLapse-Embedded Raspberry Pi backend): MIT License.

The full license texts are provided below for convenience.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Hardware License: CERN-OHL-S-2.0
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

CERN-OHL-S V2

Preamble

CERN has developed this licence to promote collaboration among hardware
designers and to provide a legal tool which supports the freedom to use,
study, modify, share and distribute hardware designs and products based on
those designs. Version 2 of the CERN Open Hardware Licence comes in three
variants: CERN-OHL-P (permissive); and two reciprocal licences: CERN-OHL-W
(weakly reciprocal) and CERN-OHL-S (strongly reciprocal).

The CERN-OHL-S is copyright CERN 2020. Anyone is welcome to use it, in unmodified
form only.

Use of this Licence does not imply any endorsement by CERN of any Licensor or
their designs nor does it imply any involvement by CERN in their development.

1 Definitions

1.1 'Licence' means this CERN-OHL-S.

1.2 'Compatible Licence' means
    a) any earlier version of the CERN Open Hardware licence, or
    b) any version of the CERN-OHL-S, or
    c) any licence which permits You to treat the Source to which it applies as
       Licensed Material under this Licence (for example CC-BY-SA 4.0).

1.3 'Source' means information such as design materials or digital code
    which can be applied to Make or test a Product or to prepare a Product for
    use, Conveyance or sale, regardless of its medium or how it is expressed. It
    may include Notices.

1.4 'Covered Source' means Source that is explicitly made available under this
    Licence.

1.5 'Product' means any device, component, work or physical object, whether in
    finished or intermediate form, arising from the use, application or
    processing of Covered Source.

1.6 'Make' means to create or configure something, whether by manufacture,
    assembly, compiling, loading or applying Covered Source or another Product or
    otherwise.

1.7 'Notice' means copyright, acknowledgement and trademark notices, Source
    location references, modification notices (subsection 3.3(b)) and all notices
    that refer to this Licence and to the disclaimer of warranties that are
    included in the Covered Source.

1.8 'Licensee' or 'You' means any person exercising rights under this Licence.

1.9 'Licensor' means a person who creates Source or modifies Covered Source and
    subsequently Conveys the resulting Covered Source under the terms and
    conditions of this Licence. A person may be a Licensee and a Licensor at the
    same time.

1.10 'Convey' means to communicate to the public or distribute.

2 Applicability

2.1 This Licence governs the use, copying, modification, Conveying of Covered
    Source and Products, and the Making of Products. By exercising any right
    granted under this Licence, You irrevocably accept these terms and conditions.

2.2 This Licence is granted by the Licensor directly to You, and shall apply
    worldwide and without limitation in time.

2.3 You shall not attempt to restrict by contract or otherwise the rights
    granted under this Licence to other Licensees.

2.4 This Licence is not intended to restrict fair use, fair dealing, or any
    other similar right.

3 Copying, Modifying and Conveying Covered Source

3.1 You may copy and Convey verbatim copies of Covered Source, in any medium,
    provided You retain all Notices.

3.2 You may modify Covered Source, other than Notices, provided that You
    license the modified Covered Source under the terms and conditions of this
    Licence. If You Convey modified Covered Source, You shall
    a) retain Notices as required in subsection 3.1; and
    b) add a Notice to the modified Covered Source stating that You have modified
       it, with the date and brief description of how You have modified it.

3.3 You may Convey Covered Source or modified Covered Source under licence
    terms which differ from the terms of this Licence provided that:
    a) You comply at all times with subsection 3.4;
    b) You provide a copy of this Licence to anyone to whom You Convey Covered
       Source or modified Covered Source; and
    c) You license the modified Covered Source under terms that effectively
       provide that the Source to any resulting Product is available to any
       person to whom the Product is made available and that it can be dealt with
       under terms which are substantially the same as this Licence.

3.4 You may Convey Covered Source or modified Covered Source in a form which is
    not immediately legible, provided that You include in any Conveyance a
    written offer to provide the Covered Source in a legible form, which shall
    remain valid for at least three years and shall be no more onerous than the
    cost of transferring the Covered Source to the person to whom the offer is
    made. You may Convey Covered Source or modified Covered Source without
    providing a copy of this Licence provided You include a URL or hyperlink to
    this Licence.

4 Making and Conveying Products

4.1 You may Make Products, and Convey them, provided that You ensure that the
    recipient of the Product has access to any Notices applicable to the Product.
    Those Notices must be accessible to the recipient as recommended by the
    FSF's (Free Software Foundation's) 'Recommended Practices for Providing
    Licensing Information'.

4.2 You must provide any Source necessary to Make or test the Product, either
    by including it in the Conveyance, or by providing a written offer to supply
    the Source on request, at a charge no more than the cost of providing the
    Source to the recipient. The offer must be valid for at least three years.

4.3 If You Convey a Product that You have Made, modified or installed using
    Covered Source, You must accompany the Product with the Source or with a
    written offer as described in subsection 4.2.

4.4 The Recipient of the Source shall benefit from the covenant in subsection
    2.2 in the same manner and to the same extent as You.

5 Patents

5.1 As a condition of exercising the rights granted under this Licence, You
    grant to the Licensor and to any other person who receives the Covered
    Source, or modified Covered Source, and to any person to whom the Product is
    made available, a perpetual, irrevocable, worldwide, royalty-free,
